<subSubSection id="53ED6543D25DF140FFAAF8DC55E9F80F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1B4836C8D25DF140FFAAF8DC55E9F80F" blockId="0.[96,1535,1860,2003]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25DF140FFAAF8DC50C3F8BE" bold="true" box="[96,251,1861,1890]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25DF140FED8F8DD516BF8BE" box="[274,339,1860,1890]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male</emphasis>
(length 7.3 mm). The specimen has the characteristic coloration described for the species, with legs light brown with darker rings and patches (
<figureCitation id="83CC2A4DD25DF140FC18F8F35468F85B" box="[978,1104,1898,1927]" captionStart="Figures 1―5" captionStartId="1.[96,188,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[97,1537,167,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-102@1.[795,1537,845,1722]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1―5. Eustiromastix falcatus Galiano male from Monte Alegre, Pará, Brazil. 1, Left palp proventral view. 2, Left palp retrolateral view. 3, Left palp ventral view. 4, Habitus dorsal view. 5, Habitus ventral view. Scale, figs. 1-3: 0.5 mm, figs. 4-5: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5092889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5092889/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figs. 4-5</figureCitation>
). Moreover, this resembles 
<taxonomicName id="DCF74D4BD25DF140FA2FF8F050E4F871" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1979" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Eustiromastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25DF140FA2FF8F050E4F871" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DCF74D4BD25DF140FEE2F81651C2F871" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1979" box="[296,506,1935,1965]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Eustiromastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macropalpus">
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25DF140FEE2F81651C2F871" box="[296,506,1935,1965]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. macropalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from them in having the palp with a shorter embolus and a flattened tibial apophysys, wider than long, and a long and curved cymbium (
<figureCitation id="83CC2A4DD25DF140FBBEF82C54D1F80F" box="[1140,1257,1973,2003]" captionStart="Figures 1―5" captionStartId="1.[96,188,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[97,1537,167,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-102@1.[795,1537,845,1722]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1―5. Eustiromastix falcatus Galiano male from Monte Alegre, Pará, Brazil. 1, Left palp proventral view. 2, Left palp retrolateral view. 3, Left palp ventral view. 4, Habitus dorsal view. 5, Habitus ventral view. Scale, figs. 1-3: 0.5 mm, figs. 4-5: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5092889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5092889/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figs. 1-3</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="7F664B39D25DF140FACFF82C55F9F80F" author="Galiano, M. E." box="[1285,1473,1973,2003]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="216 - 218" refId="ref998" refString="Galiano, M. E. 1981. Three new species of Salticidae (Araneae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 176: 216 - 218." type="journal article" year="1981">Galiano 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="4F886640D25CF141FFAAF95C5083F8C0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5092889" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5092889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5092889/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" startId="1.[96,188,1733,1757]" targetBox="[97,1537,167,1722]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="1B4836C8D25CF141FFAAF95C5083F8C0" blockId="1.[96,1536,1663,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FFAAF95C50C5F902" bold="true" box="[96,253,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figures 1―5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DCF74D4BD25CF141FECFF95D5266F902" authority="Galiano" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1981" box="[261,606,1732,1758]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Eustiromastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FECFF95D51C7F901" box="[261,511,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Eustiromastix falcatus</emphasis>
Galiano
</taxonomicName>
male from Monte Alegre, Pará, Brazil. 
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FBEFF95C5405F901" bold="true" box="[1061,1085,1733,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1,</emphasis>
Left palp proventral view. 
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FAB1F95C55A9F901" bold="true" box="[1403,1425,1733,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2,</emphasis>
Left palp retrolateral view. 
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FEF8F97C517FF921" bold="true" box="[306,327,1765,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">3,</emphasis>
Left palp ventral view. 
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FD91F97C5249F921" bold="true" box="[603,625,1765,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">4,</emphasis>
Habitus dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="2983EADAD25CF141FCA5F97C53BCF921" bold="true" box="[879,900,1765,1789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">5,</emphasis>
Habitus ventral view. Scale, figs. 1-3: 0.5 mm, figs. 4-5: 1.0 mm.
